messageBody:
I presume you mean shavian quikscript letter HE for a disunification? But that can't be right since QS HE matches Shavian VOW.

SHE will certainly need to be added since it is a deep version of THEY and both cannot be the same code in the same script. Whereas QS THEY *can* match with Shavian SURE.

My list has 22 QS additions (or disunifications, I see there is some technicality around the term but can't find the definition). Curious where you found the glyph matches for the others.

Jayson

> I have reviewed the Shavian and Quikscript repertoires. I find grounds for the following four disunifications:
>
> SHAVIAN LETTER HA-HA (existing)
> SHAVIAN QUIKSCRIPT LETTER HA-HA (new)
>
> SHAVIAN LETTER MIME (existing)
> SHAVIAN QUIKSCRIPT LETTER MAY (new)
>
> SHAVIAN LETTER NUN (existing)
> SHAVIAN QUIKSCRIPT LETTER NO (new)
>
> SHAVIAN LETTER LOLL (existing)
> SHAVIAN QUIKSCRIPT LETTER LOW (new)
>
> I find grounds for the following five disunifications:
>
> SHAVIAN QUIKSCRIPT LETTER WHY (new)
>
> SHAVIAN QUIKSCRIPT LETTER LLAN (new)
>
> SHAVIAN QUIKSCRIPT LETTER LOCH (new)
>
> SHAVIAN QUIKSCRIPT LETTER EXCITE (new)
>
> SHAVIAN QUIKSCRIPT LETTER EXAMINE (new)
>
> That would be nine new characters.
>
> Michael Everson * http://www.evertype.com/
